180","Pontefract, Yorkshire, England":"Pontefract, Jórvík, England, United Kingdom","Skellow, Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire West Riding, England, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Skotland, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1123–1179":"1123–1179","1117–1180":"1117–1180","1120–Male":"1120–Overleden","1135–1220":"1135–1220","1158–1218":"1158–1218","–Female":"Overleden","1100–1140":"1100–1140","1095–Female":"1095–Overleden","1117":"1117","1158":"1158","1179":"1179","1135":"1135","1123":"1123","1100":"1100","1220":"1220","1120":"1120","1140":"1140","1095":"1095","1218":"1218","1180":"1180","Pontefract, Yorkshire, England":"Pontefract, Yorkshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Skellow, Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire West Riding, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Scotland":"Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1123–1179":"1123–1179","1117–1180":"1117–1180","1120–Male":"1120–Deceased","1135–1220":"1135–1220","1158–1218":"1158–1218","–Female":"Deceased","1100–1140":"1100–1140","1095–Female":"1095–Deceased","1117":"1117","1158":"1158","1179":"1179","1135":"1135","1123":"1123","1100":"1100","1220":"1220","1120":"1120","1140":"1140","1095":"1095","1218":"1218","1180":"1180","Pontefract, Yorkshire, England":"Pontefract, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","Skellow, Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire West Riding, England, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Waleys","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English:","habitational name from Wales near Sheffield (South Yorkshire). The placename means ‘The Welshmen’ and denoted a settlement of Brittonic speakers living on the boundary between the Anglo-Saxon kingdoms of Northumbria and Mercia (from Old English <i>wēalas</i>, <i>walas</i>, plural of <i>walh</i>, <i>wealh</i>, originally meaning ‘Roman citizen’ and referring to the native British population, but in Old English this term later came to mean ‘serf, unfree person, foreigner’ or ‘Welshman’). See also   Wallis  .","habitational name from Wales, the country named from Old English <i>wēalas</i> ‘foreigners’ (especially those speaking Celtic or Romance languages). This meaning of the surname is quite rare."],"variants":[{"name":"Wailes","meanings":["English: variant of   Wales  ."]},{"name":"Wallis","meanings":["Scottish and English: from Anglo-Norman French <i>Waleis</i>, <i>Walais</i> ‘Welshman’, also sometimes ‘Breton’ (from Old English <i>wēalas</i>, <i>walas</i>, plural of <i>walh</i>, <i>wealh</i>, originally meaning a ‘Roman citizen’ and referring to the native British population, but in Old English this term later came to mean ‘serf, unfree person, foreigner’ or ‘Welshman’). In western and central England the medieval reference is clearly to Welshmen. In Norfolk and Lincolnshire, the reference was probably to Bretons, many of whom settled in the eastern counties after the Conquest. Compare   Welsh  ,   Walsh  . The idea that the Scottish surname refers to the Welsh-speaking Britons of Strathclyde is erroneous."]}]},{"name":"Henry","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["A perennially popular given name, of Continental Germanic origin, from <i>haim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."],"variants":[]},{"name":"le","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Lewis   or respelling of   Lou  , as borne by the impresario  Lew Grade  (  1906–98 , originally  Louis Winogradsky )."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Henry Wallensis le Waleys was born in 1123, in Pontefract, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Eimerus Galeius Walense le strange, was 23 and his mother, Amma De Grainsby, was 29. He married Agnes de Burgo. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died in 1179, in Yorkshire West Riding, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 56."},"et":{"1123–1179":"1123–1179","1117–1180":"1117–1180","1120–Male":"1120–Surnud","1135–1220":"1135–1220","1158–1218":"1158–1218","–Female":"Surnud","1100–1140":"1100–1140","1095–Female":"1095–Surnud","1117":"1117","1158":"1158","1179":"1179","1135":"1135","1123":"1123","1100":"1100","1220":"1220","1120":"1120","1140":"1140","1095":"1095","1218":"1218","1180":"1180","Pontefract, Yorkshire, England":"Pontefract, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Skellow, Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire West Riding, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1123–1179":"1123–1179","1117–1180":"1117–1180","1120–Male":"1120–Kuollut","1135–1220":"1135–1220","1158–1218":"1158–1218","–Female":"Kuollut","1100–1140":"1100–1140","1095–Female":"1095–Kuollut","1117":"1117","1158":"1158","1179":"1179","1135":"1135","1123":"1123","1100":"1100","1220":"1220","1120":"1120","1140":"1140","1095":"1095","1218":"1218","1180":"1180","Pontefract, Yorkshire, England":"Pontefract, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Skellow, Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire West Riding, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Scotland":"Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1123–1179":"1123–1179","1117–1180":"1117–1180","1120–Male":"1120–Décédé","1135–1220":"1135–1220","1158–1218":"1158–1218","–Female":"Décédée","1100–1140":"1100–1140","1095–Female":"1095–Décédée","1117":"1117","1158":"1158","1179":"1179","1135":"1135","1123":"1123","1100":"1100","1220":"1220","1120":"1120","1140":"1140","1095":"1095","1218":"1218","1180":"1180","Pontefract, Yorkshire, England":"Pontefract, Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Skellow, Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire West Riding, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Scotland":"Écosse, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Henry Wallensis le Waleys est né en 1123, à Pontefract, Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, son père, Eimerus Galeius Walense le strange, avait 23 ans et sa mère, Amma De Grainsby, avait 29 ans. Il a épousé Agnes de Burgo. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils et 1 fille. Il est décédé en 1179, à Yorkshire West Riding, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, à l’âge de 56 ans."},"de":{"1123–1179":"1123–1179","1117–1180":"1117–1180","1120–Male":"1120–Verstorben","1135–1220":"1135–1220","1158–1218":"1158–1218","–Female":"Verstorben","1100–1140":"1100–1140","1095–Female":"1095–Verstorben","1117":"1117","1158":"1158","1179":"1179","1135":"1135","1123":"1123","1100":"1100","1220":"1220","1120":"1120","1140":"1140","1095":"1095","1218":"1218","1180":"1180","Pontefract, Yorkshire, England":"Pontefract, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","Skellow, Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire West Riding, England, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Schottland, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Als Henry Wallensis le Waleys 1123 in Pontefract, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom geboren wurde, war sein Vater Eimerus Galeius Walense le strange 23 und seine Mutter Amma De Grainsby 29. Er hat Agnes de Burgo geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Sohn und 1 Tochter. Er starb 1179 im Alter von 56 Jahren in Yorkshire West Riding, England, United Kingdom."},"ht":{"1123–1179":"1123–1179","1117–1180":"1117–1180","1120–Male":"1120–Desede","1135–1220":"1135–1220","1158–1218":"1158–1218","–Female":"Desede","1100–1140":"1100–1140","1095–Female":"1095–Desede","1117":"1117","1158":"1158","1179":"1179","1135":"1135","1123":"1123","1100":"1100","1220":"1220","1120":"1120","1140":"1140","1095":"1095","1218":"1218","1180":"1180","Pontefract, Yorkshire, England":"Pontefract, Yorkshire, Angletè, United Kingdom","Skellow, Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire West Riding, Angletè, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Ecosse, United Kingdom"},"hu":{"1123–1179":"1123–1179","11